Description: Fluonic is a medical device company dedicated to making infusion drug delivery safer.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: Fluonic is a medical device company dedicated to making infusion drug delivery safer. Fluonic infusion products improve patients’ safety and compliance while improving medical staff productivity and reducing costs. Some of Fluonics' services are Infusion Pumps, urine monitoring, and artificial pancreas. Fluonic’s flow sensor operates based on a time of flight principle, where a “marker” of altered pH is created in the flow by electrolysis, and the time required for its arrival at a read electrode is recorded and converted to flow rate. Description: rSitez is the largest fan website in the world
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: rSitez roots are with building large enterprise technologies for Fortune 500 organizations including HP, Honda, Oracle, Sierra Pacific Resources, Corning, Avery Dennison and others. In 2006, during the MySpace craze and before anyone knew about Facebook we decided to build our own social networking website platform and framework. Since then we’ve created hundreds of social networking websites for a variety of industries across the globe. We focus exclusively on social media and mobile technologies. We’re based in Orlando Florida with an office in Barcelona, Spain. Our clients are quiet varied. Many of our clients are startups and entrepreneurs with a grand idea for a social networking platform. Some clients have a need for a small niche community platform. We listen, understand, nurture, and help to convert these ideas to a state-of-the art platform that our clients can be proud of. We can develop your social network with any feature that you would like. If you see the feature online somewhere then our developers will be able to developers the feature for you. If you have ideas for custom features or business models then please let us know and we will be happy to create these features for you as well. We’re happy to sign NDAs to protect any unique ideas that you have for your project. Our project start with our core framework with tons of social networking features. This framework allows us to create complex social networking sites built on a stable platform that is tried and proven with hundreds of other clients. With our UDD (Understand, Develop, Deploy) development methodology and our PHP based framework, we can rapidly develop any social networking site that you would like for your business or organization

The result is a simple, intuitive tool that the team at Avva believes can have a tremendously positive impact on any patient undergoing breast cancer treatment.

Description: Argil Data is a computer software company that develops flash based and shared storage optimized for Big Data & NoSQL apps.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Argil Data is developing an application aware, network attached, flash based storage product that is optimized for Big Data & NoSQL applications.  Argil has developed a unique “bare metal” architecture that provides shared storage optimized for Big Data, NoSQL and other “Distributed Storage System” based environments. We see that Hadoop & Big Data analytics are under constant pressure to improve performance with a minimum change in cost. In this environment, continuous & exponential data growth has made storage a constant bottleneck. We have developed an innovative Flash memory based architecture that delivers a 10X performance improvement at hard disk costs, while maintaining complete transparency and yet delivering an extensible, architecture that is tune-able to the Big Data workloads. Argil delivers all the benefits of Enterprise SANs in a highly scalable architecture, without the high cost or performance bottlenecks of today’s SANs.

Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: BankBosun helps bank C-Level executives navigate risk and discover reward. Bank executives have an incredibly difficult job. Burdensome regulation; economic, political and market volatility; restrictive credit; recruiting and retaining executive staff; opportunities to generate other types of income; portfolio, credit and duration risk management; and cyber security risk are just a few of the challenges bank leaders are facing. All of these challenges are coupled with the expectation to deliver superior results to shareholders, board of directors and all stakeholders.  Most middle market banks do not have the financial resources available to pay high-end experts to assist them through the challenging and risky seas through which bank C officers are required to navigate. Just like a ship’s captain has a boatswain available to help the ship achieve its mission, the bank captain has the BankBosun available to help the bank achieve its mission. BankBosun interviews leading experts located throughout the country in all areas of risk and opportunity impacting the banking industry, collecting strategies and tactics to help banks navigate risk and discover reward in this ecosystem.  BankBosun offers no-cost audio podcasts, video content and print media for busy professionals operating and succeeding in the banking ecosystem, providing them the opportunity to make efficient use of time to increase knowledge and awareness of issues and solutions that effect the banking industry.

Description: Card Swapp is a mobile QR code business card and contacts manager with a built in news feed to allow customers to follow business.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Card Swapp is a mobile QR code business card and contacts manager with a built in news feed to allow customers to follow your business. The Card Swapp application allows users to update their information without changing the QR code, which means the user does not need to print new business cards when they update their information.  Additionally, your contacts will receive all updates that you make about your business.  Unlike a mobile website, the Card Swapp application can work with or without an Internet connection.  Many QR scanners have a difficult time decoding vCards since there are too many variations of the vCard formats.  The Card Swapp application provides a new consistent standard, but also includes vCard 3.0 as a back up.  Card Swapp is more accurate than Optical Character Recognition (OCR) applications and works faster than business card transcription services. The Card Swapp QR code is more cost effective and efficient compared to Near Field Communication (NFC).  Businesses will appreciate the export function that allows for contacts import into Outlook, Gmail, Yahoo, and Thunderbird.  Card Swapp allows followers to quickly follow their favorite social media accounts.   Card Swapp is available on the iPhone and Android markets.

Description: Remote Access Quickbooks Software
Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: Levion is built to augment desktop QuickBooks for users who need to interact with QuickBooks remotely or from multiple devices. The software functions as a sort of "QuickBooks Essentials," presenting the basic features of QuickBooks in a fast and clean UI for working through tasks and generating documents quickly. Since Levion is browser based, it can be used on any device, though there are plans to have device specific apps in the future. Levion has full, two-way integration with QuickBooks and also updates in real time.  The Windows QuickBooks program is expansive and provides a great software base for any small business. Levion, however, gives users the ability to improve their QuickBooks system and data to conduct their business more effectively. The desktop versions of QuickBooks have always struggled to provide remote access efficiently and this is where Levion is filling the gap.  Levion's pricing model allows the current app to be used for free. However, there are plans to charge fees for added value components such as mailing out invoices, automated collection assistance and integrations with other platforms. While this is admittedly a small list, there are still many more value components currently in development.
